cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the convergence and alignment properties of gradient flow and gradient descent applied to deep linear networks. The topic of deep learning and optimization is typically covered in the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) in the analysis of the weight matrices. Additionally, the paper discusses the logistic loss function, which is commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications such as binary classification.
